WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

2
00:00:23.523 --> 00:00:25.442
Robby.

3
00:00:28.778 --> 00:00:30.279
Robby.

4
00:00:30.280 --> 00:00:31.905
College kid in respiratory
distress is here.

5
00:00:31.906 --> 00:00:33.323
- All right.
- You OK?

6
00:00:33.324 --> 00:00:35.075
Yep.

7
00:00:35.076 --> 00:00:37.119
I wanted to talk to the
patient in Central 12's son.

8
00:00:37.120 --> 00:00:38.328
but he took off.

9
00:00:38.329 --> 00:00:39.413
Is there a problem?

10
00:00:39.414 --> 00:00:40.748
Uh. according to Mom.

11
00:00:40.749 --> 00:00:41.832
she found a list of
high school girls

12
00:00:41.833 --> 00:00:44.877
that he'd like to eliminate.

13
00:00:44.878 --> 00:00:47.004
What's wrong with
kids these days?

14
00:00:47.005 --> 00:00:48.922
Uh. you mean
besides social media

15
00:00:48.923 --> 00:00:51.675
and the worldwide pandemic
and the environmental crisis?

16
00:00:51.676 --> 00:00:53.469
- Yeah. yeah. yeah.
- And gun violence?

17
00:00:53.470 --> 00:00:55.179
You're a fucking fountain
of hope today. aren't you?

18
00:00:55.180 --> 00:00:57.931
Nick Bradley. 19. found
unresponsive by parents.

19
00:00:57.932 --> 00:00:59.350
No meds. no allergies.

20
00:00:59.351 --> 00:01:00.934
On arrival. he was
barely breathing

21
00:01:00.935 --> 00:01:03.270
with pinpoint pupils.
bradycardic at 38.

22
00:01:03.271 --> 00:01:04.980
Pupils responded to Narcan.

23
00:01:04.981 --> 00:01:07.566
but we tubed him when his
respirations didn't pick up.

24
00:01:07.567 --> 00:01:09.568
Any drugs or alcohol
on the scene?

25
00:01:09.569 --> 00:01:11.111
- No.
- Signs of trauma?

26
00:01:11.112 --> 00:01:12.363
Nothing.

27
00:01:12.364 --> 00:01:14.031
OK. Open your eyes. Nick.

28
00:01:14.032 --> 00:01:16.493
On three. One. two. three.

29
00:01:18.411 --> 00:01:21.663
- Where was he found?
- In bed by his mom.

30
00:01:21.664 --> 00:01:26.168
Pupils are 6 millimeters.
non-reactive.

31
00:01:26.169 --> 00:01:28.671
Heart rate's 64.
BP is cycling.

32
00:01:28.672 --> 00:01:31.465
No response to pain. GCS 3.

33
00:01:31.466 --> 00:01:34.009
- Does that fit any toxidrome?
- No.

34
00:01:34.010 --> 00:01:36.470
If it was just
opiates with Narcan.

35
00:01:36.471 --> 00:01:38.806
he'd be breathing on his own.

36
00:01:38.807 --> 00:01:41.016
Uh. beta blockers shouldn't
get pinpoint pupils.

37
00:01:41.017 --> 00:01:42.518
Maybe parents had some

38
00:01:42.519 --> 00:01:43.602
prescription meds
in their bathroom.

39
00:01:43.603 --> 00:01:45.270
They're on their way.

40
00:01:45.271 --> 00:01:47.398
<i>Code trauma. tier
1. ETA five minutes.</i>

41
00:01:47.399 --> 00:01:49.733
That's a stand-up scooter
rider versus car door.

42
00:01:49.734 --> 00:01:51.985
- No helmet.
- No blood in the belly.

43
00:01:51.986 --> 00:01:57.116
No pericardial effusion.
and lungs are up.

44
00:01:57.117 --> 00:01:58.992
Hemocue's good. 15.

45
00:01:58.993 --> 00:02:01.829
- BP 84 over 58.
- OK.

46
00:02:01.830 --> 00:02:03.789
What's your plan. Dr. Collins?

47
00:02:03.790 --> 00:02:07.751
Um. push dose epi.
0.1 milligram.

48
00:02:07.752 --> 00:02:10.170
Foley for urine.
stabilize for CT.

49
00:02:10.171 --> 00:02:13.425
and throw a wide net.

50
00:02:17.554 --> 00:02:18.846
Where... where
are we going now?

51
00:02:18.847 --> 00:02:20.681
We need the room
for someone else.

52
00:02:20.682 --> 00:02:23.685
but you can rest in the hall
till we get your labs back.

53
00:02:25.353 --> 00:02:27.855
Your parents must be proud.

54
00:02:27.856 --> 00:02:30.065
Having a son for a doctor.

55
00:02:30.066 --> 00:02:32.735
Yeah. I guess.

56
00:02:32.736 --> 00:02:34.445
Um. you know.

57
00:02:34.446 --> 00:02:38.532
I was the first one in my
family to go to college.

58
00:02:38.533 --> 00:02:42.369
You know. they sacrificed
a lot to get me here.

59
00:02:42.370 --> 00:02:43.954
How's your pain. Mr. Milton?

60
00:02:43.955 --> 00:02:45.414
Uh. I'm fine.

61
00:02:45.415 --> 00:02:46.999
Could use a latte. though.

62
00:02:47.000 --> 00:02:49.251
That could bring back
the gallstone pain.

63
00:02:49.252 --> 00:02:50.753
How about a bourbon?

64
00:02:50.754 --> 00:02:52.463
It's barely 8:00.

65
00:02:52.464 --> 00:02:54.798
Uh. how about some ice chips?

66
00:02:54.799 --> 00:02:56.800
No. thanks.

67
00:02:56.801 --> 00:02:58.594
I prefer my whiskey neat.

68
00:02:58.595 --> 00:03:00.013
Yeah. that's not happening.

69
00:03:04.768 --> 00:03:07.478
Systolic back down to 90.

70
00:03:07.479 --> 00:03:09.480
Another 0.1 of epi.

71
00:03:09.481 --> 00:03:13.233
Flaccid paralysis of
all four extremities.

72
00:03:13.234 --> 00:03:16.111
No eye movement with ice water.

73
00:03:16.112 --> 00:03:17.696
So no brainstem function.

74
00:03:17.697 --> 00:03:19.073
Due to?

75
00:03:19.074 --> 00:03:21.533
Hypoxic injury.
massive hemorrhage.

76
00:03:21.534 --> 00:03:23.744
Samira. escort him to CT.

77
00:03:23.745 --> 00:03:25.788
Take the drug box with you.

78
00:03:25.789 --> 00:03:27.331
Call me if you need me.

79
00:03:27.332 --> 00:03:29.875
Hey. are you OK?

80
00:03:29.876 --> 00:03:31.627
- Yep.
- Are you sure?

81
00:03:31.628 --> 00:03:33.921
Have you ever had
to worry about me?

82
00:03:33.922 --> 00:03:36.256
No. but it never
hurts to check in.

83
00:03:36.257 --> 00:03:38.092
It's part of my job.

84
00:03:38.093 --> 00:03:40.427
Consider yourself checked in.

85
00:03:40.428 --> 00:03:41.930
OK.

86
00:03:42.972 --> 00:03:45.307
Ah. ah. ah. ah. ah.

87
00:03:45.308 --> 00:03:46.600
Got something?

88
00:03:46.601 --> 00:03:48.227
Oh. I had a case
for Dr. Collins.

89
00:03:48.228 --> 00:03:50.604
- May I see?
- Yeah.

90
00:03:50.605 --> 00:03:53.899
A 68-year-old male.
history of hypertension.

91
00:03:53.900 --> 00:03:55.609
one hour of right
upper quadrant pain

92
00:03:55.610 --> 00:03:57.861
after eating a fatty
meal. now resolved.

93
00:03:57.862 --> 00:03:59.279
Afebrile. non-tender.

94
00:03:59.280 --> 00:04:01.198
There was a gallstone
present on POCUS.

95
00:04:01.199 --> 00:04:03.701
EKG shows no acute
ischemic changes.

96
00:04:03.702 --> 00:04:05.994
but I'm still waiting
on LFTs and lipase.

97
00:04:05.995 --> 00:04:08.497
Why did you order the EKG?

98
00:04:08.498 --> 00:04:11.750
The nurse suggested it to
rule out any cardiac issues.

99
00:04:11.751 --> 00:04:14.294
Well. good call on
both your parts.

100
00:04:14.295 --> 00:04:15.629
Nurses know what they're doing.

101
00:04:15.630 --> 00:04:17.089
Never hesitate to
listen to them.

102
00:04:17.090 --> 00:04:18.674
Come find me when
those labs are back.

103
00:04:18.675 --> 00:04:20.134
- Hey. how's that finger?
- Oh. it's nothing.

104
00:04:20.135 --> 00:04:21.593
- Dr. Robby?
- Yep?

105
00:04:21.594 --> 00:04:23.012
The son and daughter
of Mr. Spencer

106
00:04:23.013 --> 00:04:24.596
from assisted
living. they're here.

107
00:04:24.597 --> 00:04:26.850
OK. I'll be right there.

108
00:04:33.732 --> 00:04:36.859
Your father has pneumonia and
a condition called sepsis.

109
00:04:36.860 --> 00:04:38.777
What is... what
is that exactly?

110
00:04:38.778 --> 00:04:41.113
It means that the bacteria
has spread from his lung

111
00:04:41.114 --> 00:04:42.698
to his bloodstream.

112
00:04:42.699 --> 00:04:45.242
So far. he's been responding
well to treatment.

113
00:04:45.243 --> 00:04:47.661
Hey. Pop.

114
00:04:47.662 --> 00:04:49.956
It's Helen and Jereme.

115
00:04:51.833 --> 00:04:54.168
Jereme...

116
00:04:54.169 --> 00:04:56.003
Hillary...

117
00:04:56.004 --> 00:04:57.212
Boob...

118
00:04:57.213 --> 00:04:58.923
Fud.

119
00:05:00.925 --> 00:05:03.802
It's the "Nowhere Man"
from "Yellow Submarine."

120
00:05:03.803 --> 00:05:06.138
It's what he used to call me
when I didn't do my homework.

121
00:05:06.139 --> 00:05:07.931
Is this his baseline?

122
00:05:07.932 --> 00:05:10.143
He has good days and bad days.

123
00:05:11.686 --> 00:05:13.855
Why don't we step out
for one more second?

124
00:05:18.485 --> 00:05:20.652
So your father came in
with low blood pressure.

125
00:05:20.653 --> 00:05:21.987
which is improving.

126
00:05:21.988 --> 00:05:23.614
Can he go back to
assisted living?

127
00:05:23.615 --> 00:05:25.449
Eventually. we hope so.

128
00:05:25.450 --> 00:05:27.242
Your dad has an
advanced directive

129
00:05:27.243 --> 00:05:28.952
expressing his wishes.
which says that

130
00:05:28.953 --> 00:05:31.288
IV fluids and
medications are OK.

131
00:05:31.289 --> 00:05:33.749
but no artificial
life support. no CPR.

132
00:05:33.750 --> 00:05:36.543
He doesn't want a bunch of
machines keeping him alive.

133
00:05:36.544 --> 00:05:38.212
OK.

134
00:05:38.213 --> 00:05:40.005
Then we will
continue with oxygen

135
00:05:40.006 --> 00:05:42.508
and IV fluids and antibiotics.

136
00:05:42.509 --> 00:05:44.176
but if his lungs stop working.

137
00:05:44.177 --> 00:05:45.636
we're not going to place
a tube in his windpipe

138
00:05:45.637 --> 00:05:46.762
for a breathing machine.

139
00:05:46.763 --> 00:05:49.223
But pneumonia is treatable?

140
00:05:49.224 --> 00:05:51.975
Most of the time. it is.

141
00:05:51.976 --> 00:05:53.018
But if he can get
better in a week.

142
00:05:53.019 --> 00:05:54.269
then put him on a machine.

143
00:05:54.270 --> 00:05:56.105
That's not what <i>he</i> wanted.

144
00:05:56.106 --> 00:05:58.107
Do either of you have
durable power of attorney

145
00:05:58.108 --> 00:05:59.692
for health care?

146
00:05:59.693 --> 00:06:00.943
- Yes.
- We both do.

147
00:06:00.944 --> 00:06:02.111
OK.

148
00:06:02.112 --> 00:06:03.612
Well. this is a decision

149
00:06:03.613 --> 00:06:04.988
that does not need
to be made right now.

150
00:06:04.989 --> 00:06:06.532
Why don't you think about it?

151
00:06:06.533 --> 00:06:08.075
Talk about it.

152
00:06:08.076 --> 00:06:11.954
If things get worse.
sometimes allowing

153
00:06:11.955 --> 00:06:15.000
for a comfortable natural death
can be the most humane path.

154
00:06:18.420 --> 00:06:21.255
No routine cases until
we assess the tier 1.

155
00:06:21.256 --> 00:06:22.256
Thanks.

156
00:06:22.257 --> 00:06:24.842
Dr. Langdon?

157
00:06:24.843 --> 00:06:27.970
So. uh. how was the VA?

158
00:06:27.971 --> 00:06:30.723
Yeah. it was. uh good.
uh. you know. challenging.

159
00:06:30.724 --> 00:06:33.350
I learned a ton.
I just think it...

160
00:06:33.351 --> 00:06:34.685
maybe it should be mandatory

161
00:06:34.686 --> 00:06:35.728
that all doctors
spend time there.

162
00:06:35.729 --> 00:06:37.229
like. on a regular basis

163
00:06:37.230 --> 00:06:39.231
because of all they've
sacrificed for us.

164
00:06:39.232 --> 00:06:41.984
That's a nice thought.
Why'd you choose the Pitt?

165
00:06:41.985 --> 00:06:43.444
Oh. I have a sister
with special needs

166
00:06:43.445 --> 00:06:45.070
and she got into this
really great facility

167
00:06:45.071 --> 00:06:46.447
here in Pittsburgh.

168
00:06:46.448 --> 00:06:48.157
And PTMC has such
a great reputation.

169
00:06:48.158 --> 00:06:49.992
I thought. you know.
it'd be a good fit.

170
00:06:49.993 --> 00:06:51.076
Can I present my
headache to you?

171
00:06:51.077 --> 00:06:52.619
Uh. yeah. what do you got?

172
00:06:52.620 --> 00:06:54.496
A 36-year-old woman
with severe headache

173
00:06:54.497 --> 00:06:56.331
due to paracervical
trigger point.

174
00:06:56.332 --> 00:06:59.043
Her pain went from 11 to zero
after 2 ccs of IM Marcaine

175
00:06:59.044 --> 00:07:00.336
- to the...
- Wait. wait. wait.

176
00:07:00.337 --> 00:07:01.837
You did a trigger
point injection

177
00:07:01.838 --> 00:07:03.547
- before presenting the case?
- Yeah. I...

178
00:07:03.548 --> 00:07:05.799
Interns always present first.

179
00:07:05.800 --> 00:07:07.092
I spent a month at the
pain clinic at Hopkins.

180
00:07:07.093 --> 00:07:08.844
- No. it's not OK.
- Incoming!

181
00:07:08.845 --> 00:07:10.804
- I'm very comfortable with...
- It's definitely not OK.

182
00:07:10.805 --> 00:07:12.598
23-year-old Ben
Kemper. no helmet.

183
00:07:12.599 --> 00:07:14.433
got doored riding an e-scooter.

184
00:07:14.434 --> 00:07:16.435
Neck versus handlebar then
face-planted to the pavement.

185
00:07:16.436 --> 00:07:18.020
Obvious facial fractures.

186
00:07:18.021 --> 00:07:19.981
but alert and oriented
with good vitals.

187
00:07:22.359 --> 00:07:23.693
Here we go.

188
00:07:25.320 --> 00:07:27.530
One. two. three.

189
00:07:29.949 --> 00:07:31.241
How are we doing. Ben?

190
00:07:31.242 --> 00:07:33.619
Blood. back in my throat.

191
00:07:33.620 --> 00:07:35.412
That's probably
from the nosebleed.

192
00:07:35.413 --> 00:07:37.289
Short Rapid Rhino. please.

193
00:07:37.290 --> 00:07:40.501
Tachy at 120. pulse
ox borderline at 90.

194
00:07:40.502 --> 00:07:41.877
Blow by at 15 liters for now.

195
00:07:41.878 --> 00:07:43.462
- Neck contusion.
- BP 138 over 84.

196
00:07:43.463 --> 00:07:45.130
Larynx shifted to the
right. no crepitance.

197
00:07:45.131 --> 00:07:47.132
4 of morphine.

198
00:07:47.133 --> 00:07:51.637
I'm going to stick something in
your nose to stop the bleeding.

199
00:07:51.638 --> 00:07:53.347
No hemotympanum.

200
00:07:53.348 --> 00:07:56.225
Inflate the balloon.

201
00:07:56.226 --> 00:07:58.686
How about now. Ben?

202
00:07:58.687 --> 00:08:01.188
- Better.
- What's up?

203
00:08:01.189 --> 00:08:04.401
Good vitals. A and
O. let's have a look.

204
00:08:08.279 --> 00:08:09.613
Ouch.

205
00:08:09.614 --> 00:08:12.324
- Floating face.
- Le Fort III fracture.

206
00:08:12.325 --> 00:08:14.743
You don't see that every day.
OK. let's prep for airway.

207
00:08:14.744 --> 00:08:17.038
Double setup just in case.

208
00:08:30.885 --> 00:08:34.096
- Nice work.
- Thanks.

209
00:08:34.097 --> 00:08:36.181
All right. Mr. Tagari.
you are good to go.

210
00:08:36.182 --> 00:08:37.850
Oh. thank you.

211
00:08:37.851 --> 00:08:42.187
Remember. 10% off for
doctors and nurses.

212
00:08:42.188 --> 00:08:43.605
I'm a student doctor.

213
00:08:43.606 --> 00:08:45.649
Oh. right. Sorry.

214
00:08:45.650 --> 00:08:48.027
- I hit my head. remember?
- Well. my son loves pizza.

215
00:08:48.028 --> 00:08:49.611
so I will take you up
on it for sure. OK?

216
00:08:49.612 --> 00:08:50.863
- Thank you. Thank you.
- Thank you.

217
00:08:50.864 --> 00:08:52.614
- Wait for a nurse.
- OK. thanks.

218
00:08:52.615 --> 00:08:54.575
Hi.

219
00:08:54.576 --> 00:08:57.161
I just realized it sounds like
I always feed my kid junk food.

220
00:08:57.162 --> 00:08:58.370
- Oh.
- You know?

221
00:08:58.371 --> 00:08:59.913
Pizza. s'mores.

222
00:08:59.914 --> 00:09:02.791
No. no. please. I... I
like pizza and s'mores.

223
00:09:02.792 --> 00:09:05.627
- Who doesn't?
- Mm.

224
00:09:05.628 --> 00:09:09.173
- How many kids do you have?
- Just one. Harrison.

225
00:09:09.174 --> 00:09:11.592
He's 11 now.

226
00:09:11.593 --> 00:09:12.968
What does your husband do?

227
00:09:12.969 --> 00:09:14.928
No husband. just me and my son.

228
00:09:14.929 --> 00:09:16.388
I take it you don't have kids?

229
00:09:16.389 --> 00:09:18.766
I... I don't mean on
account of your age.

230
00:09:18.767 --> 00:09:20.392
Or maybe I do.

231
00:09:20.393 --> 00:09:22.353
I mean. most medical
students don't have kids.

232
00:09:22.354 --> 00:09:25.939
Oh. yeah. no. no. Um. no kids.

233
00:09:25.940 --> 00:09:29.234
Just not even a boyfriend.
Uh. it's just school for now.

234
00:09:29.235 --> 00:09:31.236
Yeah. That'll keep
you pretty busy.

235
00:09:31.237 --> 00:09:33.572
I do not miss it.

236
00:09:33.573 --> 00:09:35.866
Must have been difficult
as a young mother.

237
00:09:35.867 --> 00:09:37.368
It had its moments.

238
00:09:37.369 --> 00:09:39.078
but my life has been
full of challenges.

239
00:09:39.079 --> 00:09:42.373
and med school was not one
of the hardest. by far.

240
00:09:42.374 --> 00:09:44.708
It was one of the most
rewarding. though.

241
00:09:44.709 --> 00:09:48.462
- Other than having my son.
- Hey.

242
00:09:48.463 --> 00:09:50.923
Facial lash with possible
foreign object in the eye.

243
00:09:50.924 --> 00:09:54.343
which is always a solid
7 on the WMMV Scale.

244
00:09:54.344 --> 00:09:56.054
What Makes Mateo Vomit.

245
00:09:59.307 --> 00:10:01.975
- You OK?
- Yeah.

246
00:10:01.976 --> 00:10:05.562
Yeah. Um. he's funny. the...

247
00:10:05.563 --> 00:10:06.980
- the nurse.
- Oh. Mateo.

248
00:10:06.981 --> 00:10:08.692
You can say his name.

249
00:10:09.984 --> 00:10:12.319
Um. yeah. uh...

250
00:10:12.320 --> 00:10:15.490
a foreign object in the eye
could be really serious.

251
00:10:22.330 --> 00:10:25.457
Hey. Fruitcake.

252
00:10:25.458 --> 00:10:26.875
Hey. I'm talking
to you. Fruitcake.

253
00:10:26.876 --> 00:10:28.627
Myrna. I told you
a hundred times

254
00:10:28.628 --> 00:10:31.046
my name is Dr. Robby.

255
00:10:31.047 --> 00:10:33.173
You want to see my vagina?

256
00:10:33.174 --> 00:10:35.259
