00:20:44.661 --> 00:20:46.287
if it doesn't even work?

512
00:20:54.045 --> 00:20:55.421
Sorry.

513
00:20:55.422 --> 00:20:57.423
You're doing great.
Take your time.

514
00:20:57.424 --> 00:20:58.465
You OK?

515
00:20:58.466 --> 00:20:59.967
I am... yeah.

516
00:20:59.968 --> 00:21:01.385
I get frustrated when
I can't do things.

517
00:21:01.386 --> 00:21:02.886
or at least it looks like it.

518
00:21:02.887 --> 00:21:05.097
Yeah. you and me both.

519
00:21:05.098 --> 00:21:08.434
Thanks. but my frustration
manifests itself emotionally.

520
00:21:08.435 --> 00:21:10.310
and then. uh. I get upset.

521
00:21:10.311 --> 00:21:12.146
and then it looks like
I can't handle things.

522
00:21:12.147 --> 00:21:14.314
and. you know. then I can't
cry in front of the patient

523
00:21:14.315 --> 00:21:15.524
because no one wants to
see their doctor cry.

524
00:21:15.525 --> 00:21:17.276
That's just a big red flag.

525
00:21:17.277 --> 00:21:20.530
You just did a perfect
crike. You're doing great.

526
00:21:23.700 --> 00:21:25.659
Hey. you! Pasty white!

527
00:21:25.660 --> 00:21:27.119
How about a sandwich?

528
00:21:27.120 --> 00:21:30.414
Uh. what brings you
here today. sir?

529
00:21:30.415 --> 00:21:33.292
I'm here for a fucking sandwich.

530
00:21:33.293 --> 00:21:35.044
OK.

531
00:21:35.045 --> 00:21:37.963
OK. uh. excuse me...

532
00:21:37.964 --> 00:21:39.381
- Perlah.
- Perlah.

533
00:21:39.382 --> 00:21:41.258
Can this patient get a sandwich?

534
00:21:41.259 --> 00:21:42.718
I already gave you
a sandwich. Earl.

535
00:21:42.719 --> 00:21:45.637
I ain't ate this whole week.

536
00:21:45.638 --> 00:21:47.306
Sure.

537
00:21:47.307 --> 00:21:49.141
Give him another sandwich.
They're on the food cart.

538
00:21:49.142 --> 00:21:50.351
Just make sure
it's not egg salad.

539
00:21:50.352 --> 00:21:51.894
or he'll throw it on the floor.

540
00:21:51.895 --> 00:21:53.772
OK. Good to know. Thanks.

541
00:22:08.328 --> 00:22:09.953
Any quick ones up here?

542
00:22:09.954 --> 00:22:11.747
It's only 8:30. and
Robby's already on my case

543
00:22:11.748 --> 00:22:13.707
for being too slow.

544
00:22:13.708 --> 00:22:14.833
I can usually at
least make it to lunch

545
00:22:14.834 --> 00:22:16.460
before he starts hounding me.

546
00:22:16.461 --> 00:22:18.337
Cut him a little
slack today. OK?

547
00:22:18.338 --> 00:22:20.923
It's the anniversary
of Dr. Adamson's death.

548
00:22:20.924 --> 00:22:23.550
That's sad.

549
00:22:23.551 --> 00:22:26.220
But it's still no reason
to take it out on me.

550
00:22:26.221 --> 00:22:27.930
I'm just saying.

551
00:22:27.931 --> 00:22:30.474
- Dr. Mohan?
- Samira. please.

552
00:22:30.475 --> 00:22:32.476
I just wanted to apologize.

553
00:22:32.477 --> 00:22:35.521
When my phone went off earlier.
that was really unprofessional.

554
00:22:35.522 --> 00:22:36.897
Don't sweat it. Trust me.

555
00:22:36.898 --> 00:22:38.273
We need to laugh.

556
00:22:38.274 --> 00:22:39.817
Otherwise. we'd
never stop crying.

557
00:22:39.818 --> 00:22:41.151
Thank you.

558
00:22:41.152 --> 00:22:42.569
Besides. with all the craziness

559
00:22:42.570 --> 00:22:43.904
that comes through
here every hour.

560
00:22:43.905 --> 00:22:45.698
nobody cares or notices.

561
00:22:45.699 --> 00:22:48.075
Got an unresponsive
unhoused man coming in.

562
00:22:48.076 --> 00:22:52.163
Might be a good teaching
case. Funky Music.

563
00:22:54.290 --> 00:22:55.624
Let's go.

564
00:22:55.625 --> 00:22:57.001
Caucasian male.

565
00:22:57.002 --> 00:22:58.627
approximately 60
to 70 years old.

566
00:22:58.628 --> 00:23:01.965
found unresponsive. No
signs of trauma. no ID.

567
00:23:03.425 --> 00:23:05.092
On three.

568
00:23:05.093 --> 00:23:07.387
One. two. three.

569
00:23:09.681 --> 00:23:12.099
Oof. Did you take anything?

570
00:23:12.100 --> 00:23:13.600
I smell the alcohol from here.

571
00:23:13.601 --> 00:23:14.810
This guy's wearing
the spring. summer.

572
00:23:14.811 --> 00:23:15.979
and fall collection.

573
00:23:17.188 --> 00:23:18.355
Oh! Whoa!

574
00:23:18.356 --> 00:23:20.107
- Jesus. uh...
- Oh. oh. oh!

575
00:23:20.108 --> 00:23:21.191
What the...

576
00:23:21.192 --> 00:23:22.526
Oh!

577
00:23:22.527 --> 00:23:25.195
Uh. what's wrong?
What's going on?

578
00:23:25.196 --> 00:23:28.157
Patient tested
positive for rats.

579
00:23:28.158 --> 00:23:29.575
No.

580
00:23:29.576 --> 00:23:33.120
If it matters. I
only counted three.

581
00:23:33.121 --> 00:23:34.622
Oh. there goes one.

582
00:23:39.169 --> 00:23:41.253
Because your son tested
positive for THC.

583
00:23:41.254 --> 00:23:43.422
the psychoactive
ingredient in cannabis.

584
00:23:43.423 --> 00:23:45.090
we're going to have to
admit him for overnight

585
00:23:45.091 --> 00:23:47.092
observation and monitoring.

586
00:23:47.093 --> 00:23:49.178
And what about his brain?

587
00:23:49.179 --> 00:23:51.597
Is there a chance that much
pot is going to do some damage?

588
00:23:51.598 --> 00:23:53.015
He's only four.

589
00:23:53.016 --> 00:23:54.683
The honest answer
is we don't know.

590
00:23:54.684 --> 00:23:56.268
There haven't been
any long-term studies.

591
00:23:56.269 --> 00:23:58.020
but the fact that this
is a one-time occurrence

592
00:23:58.021 --> 00:24:00.230
suggests that there should
be no long-term effects.

593
00:24:00.231 --> 00:24:01.940
But you don't know.

594
00:24:01.941 --> 00:24:04.109
So my son could end up
with learning disabilities.

595
00:24:04.110 --> 00:24:06.612
psychiatric problems. or
even autism because of this.

596
00:24:06.613 --> 00:24:08.405
There's no evidence to
suggest any of that.

597
00:24:08.406 --> 00:24:11.158
Hello. I'm Kiara Alfaro.

598
00:24:11.159 --> 00:24:13.077
I'm the department
social worker.

599
00:24:13.078 --> 00:24:15.996
Kiara will help you
navigate the next steps.

600
00:24:15.997 --> 00:24:17.289
What steps?

601
00:24:17.290 --> 00:24:18.832
Well. a case like this

602
00:24:18.833 --> 00:24:21.877
requires mandatory
reporting to child services

603
00:24:21.878 --> 00:24:23.962
- and sometimes law enforcement.
- No.

604
00:24:23.963 --> 00:24:25.130
Why... why do you have
to involve the police?

605
00:24:25.131 --> 00:24:26.465
It's a controlled substance.

606
00:24:26.466 --> 00:24:28.133
They're not taking my kid away.

607
00:24:28.134 --> 00:24:30.010
- They were pot gummies.
- No one's suggesting that.

608
00:24:30.011 --> 00:24:32.137
Well. fuck your suggestions!
No one is touching my child!

609
00:24:32.138 --> 00:24:33.639
In fact. we're leaving.

610
00:24:33.640 --> 00:24:35.140
Well you... no. you
can't take your son.

611
00:24:35.141 --> 00:24:36.725
He could stop breathing.
He could have a seizure.

612
00:24:36.726 --> 00:24:38.310
- I will observe him at home.
- Amanda. please.

613
00:24:38.311 --> 00:24:39.978
- Fuck off. Drew.
- Get security.

614
00:24:39.979 --> 00:24:41.355
If you can't cooperate.

615
00:24:41.356 --> 00:24:42.773
I'm going to have
to ask you to leave.

616
00:24:42.774 --> 00:24:44.233
Amanda. please. He
needs to stay here.

617
00:24:44.234 --> 00:24:45.984
And you need to get
a fucking hotel.

618
00:24:45.985 --> 00:24:47.277
Your son can't
leave the hospital.

619
00:24:47.278 --> 00:24:48.612
but I can have you removed.

620
00:24:48.613 --> 00:24:49.947
Don't you dare touch me.

621
00:24:49.948 --> 00:24:51.573
Get out! All of you!

622
00:24:51.574 --> 00:24:53.742
Mrs. Jones. I know this
is scary and stressful.

623
00:24:53.743 --> 00:24:55.911
Oh. fuck you! Fuck
you! This is my son.

624
00:24:55.912 --> 00:24:57.246
My son! And nobody
is touching him!

625
00:24:57.247 --> 00:24:58.914
Whoa. whoa. whoa.
What's going on?

626
00:24:58.915 --> 00:25:00.332
- How can I help you?
- By backing the fuck off!

627
00:25:00.333 --> 00:25:01.917
Mom's worried about
a CYF investigation.

628
00:25:01.918 --> 00:25:03.919
- Amanda. just calm down!
- OK. OK. OK. enough!

629
00:25:03.920 --> 00:25:05.337
This is a hospital.

630
00:25:05.338 --> 00:25:06.964
This isn't "The
Jerry Springer Show."

631
00:25:06.965 --> 00:25:09.425
Ma'am. nobody's trying
to take your child.

632
00:25:09.426 --> 00:25:11.135
so why don't you
stay here with him

633
00:25:11.136 --> 00:25:12.886
while your husband talks to
our social worker outside

634
00:25:12.887 --> 00:25:14.555
and straightens all this out?

635
00:25:14.556 --> 00:25:16.932
Well. I don't want him
speaking for me and my son.

636
00:25:16.933 --> 00:25:18.892
Well. it is either you or him.

637
00:25:18.893 --> 00:25:21.895
Your son is not leaving.
but you can be escorted out

638
00:25:21.896 --> 00:25:23.981
and even arrested if
you refuse to cooperate.

639
00:25:23.982 --> 00:25:25.482
Nobody wants that.

640
00:25:25.483 --> 00:25:27.485
So you tell us. What
do you want to do?

641
00:25:30.488 --> 00:25:33.240
- I'm staying with my son.
- OK. great.

642
00:25:33.241 --> 00:25:35.075
You do that.

643
00:25:35.076 --> 00:25:37.453
We all on the same page here?

644
00:25:37.454 --> 00:25:38.871
Thank you. Olsen.

645
00:25:38.872 --> 00:25:39.872
- You know where to find me.
- You OK?

646
00:25:39.873 --> 00:25:41.665
Yeah. we got this.

647
00:25:41.666 --> 00:25:43.459
- All good.
- It's all yours.

648
00:25:43.460 --> 00:25:45.211
Mrs. Jones. we just
have a couple things.

649
00:25:48.590 --> 00:25:49.840
Everything all right out there?

650
00:25:49.841 --> 00:25:52.176
Yeah. just another
day in paradise.

651
00:25:52.177 --> 00:25:54.094
- How are you feeling?
- Better.

652
00:25:54.095 --> 00:25:56.638
- Where's David?
- He left.

653
00:25:56.639 --> 00:25:59.516
He said he had to
get back to school.

654
00:25:59.517 --> 00:26:01.101
Oh.

655
00:26:01.102 --> 00:26:02.895
Um. maybe you could
try calling him.

656
00:26:02.896 --> 00:26:04.105
get him to come back.

657
00:26:06.858 --> 00:26:09.735
What's going to
happen to him if I do?

658
00:26:09.736 --> 00:26:11.987
Hopefully he'll be willing
to talk to somebody.

659
00:26:11.988 --> 00:26:14.615
- Will you talk to him?
- I can try.

660
00:26:14.616 --> 00:26:17.368
I don't think he
wanted to talk to me.

661
00:26:17.369 --> 00:26:19.703
Have you shared with anyone

662
00:26:19.704 --> 00:26:21.789
about the writings
of his you found?

663
00:26:21.790 --> 00:26:23.582
No.

664
00:26:23.583 --> 00:26:25.292
I didn't know who to tell.

665
00:26:25.293 --> 00:26:27.544
I just don't want
to see him get hurt.

666
00:26:27.545 --> 00:26:29.381
Neither do we.

667
00:26:38.765 --> 00:26:40.099
It's just going
straight to voicemail.

668
00:26:40.100 --> 00:26:42.185
Maybe if you can text him.

669
00:26:54.531 --> 00:26:56.615
He's not texting back.

670
00:26:56.616 --> 00:26:58.200
Oh. I'm sorry about all this.

671
00:26:58.201 --> 00:26:59.743
It's OK. it's OK.

672
00:26:59.744 --> 00:27:02.955
What are you doing for
David is very brave.

673
00:27:02.956 --> 00:27:04.206
I'm his mother.

674
00:27:04.207 --> 00:27:06.334
I'll do anything to protect him.

675
00:27:08.336 --> 00:27:09.586
Do you think he
would hurt anyone?

676
00:27:09.587 --> 00:27:11.256
No.

677
00:27:12.966 --> 00:27:16.969
But...

678
00:27:16.970 --> 00:27:20.723
I'm sure a lot of
parents felt that way

679
00:27:20.724 --> 00:27:23.685
before their children
did unspeakable things.

680
00:27:26.354 --> 00:27:27.771
Does he have any
history of violence?

681
00:27:27.772 --> 00:27:29.189
Has he ever been in any trouble?

682
00:27:29.190 --> 00:27:30.649
No. never.

683
00:27:30.650 --> 00:27:33.068
He's very quiet.

684
00:27:33.069 --> 00:27:35.487
And he takes great care of me.

685
00:27:35.488 --> 00:27:40.993
He... he's struggled
with his father's death.

686
00:27:40.994 --> 00:27:42.953
We both have.

687
00:27:42.954 --> 00:27:45.247
Flight is ten minutes out
with an electrocution.

688
00:27:45.248 --> 00:27:48.334
OK. grab Collins.
I'll be right there.

689
00:27:48.335 --> 00:27:49.752
Keep trying to reach him.

690
00:27:49.753 --> 00:27:51.378
If you do. have
someone come find me.

691
00:27:51.379 --> 00:27:53.756
- OK?
- OK.

692
00:27:53.757 --> 00:27:55.883
- Thank you.
- Of course.

693
00:27:55.884 --> 00:27:58.052
- You got some good news for me?
- I sure do.

694
00:27:58.053 --> 00:27:59.678
There are two rooms
in ICU being cleaned.

695
00:27:59.679 --> 00:28:01.430
- They'll be ready by now.
- Great.

696
00:28:01.431 --> 00:28:02.556
And I got bagels in the lounge.

697
00:28:02.557 --> 00:28:04.100
Nice job. Thank you.

698
00:28:06.603 --> 00:28:09.063
- Is it true?
- You have to be more specific.

699
00:28:09.064 --> 00:28:10.689
Are there rats in the ED?

700
00:28:10.690 --> 00:28:13.025
Uh. apparently. if
somebody already snitched.

701
00:28:13.026 --> 00:28:15.486
Do you know how bad this looks?

702
00:28:15.487 --> 00:28:17.488
One more reason to
shutter this place.

703
00:28:17.489 --> 00:28:19.698
Only the emergency
department admits rats.

704
00:28:19.699 --> 00:28:21.283
Emergency department
would never admit rats.

705
00:28:21.284 --> 00:28:22.868
unless they had the
right insurance.

706
00:28:22.869 --> 00:28:24.244
Did you catch any of them?

707
00:28:24.245 --> 00:28:26.038
One. and I charged
him for a full visit.

708
00:28:26.039 --> 00:28:27.581
I'm glad you think
this is funny.

709
00:28:27.582 --> 00:28:28.749
I'm sorry that you don't.

710
00:28:28.750 --> 00:28:30.542
Did you call an exterminator?

711
00:28:30.543 --> 00:28:32.337
He's waiting on
a second opinion.

712
00:28:33.755 --> 00:28:35.547
You're pushing your luck today.

713
00:28:35.548 --> 00:28:36.840
Don't worry. Last I heard.

714
00:28:36.841 --> 00:28:38.217
they were headed
for the cafeteria.

715
00:28:38.218 --> 00:28:39.385
so they should be
dead within the hour.

716
00:28:39.386 --> 00:28:40.844
OK.

717
00:28:40.845 --> 00:28:43.723
- I'll be here all week.
- Or maybe not.

718
00:28:47.435 --> 00:28:49.603
Drug-seeking woman
kicked off the city bus

719
00:28:49.604 --> 00:28:50.979
for disrupting and
disturbing passengers.

720
00:28:50.980 --> 00:28:52.564
I called 911!

721
00:28:52.565 --> 00:28:54.358
She's been screaming
for narcotics nonstop.

722
00:28:54.359 --> 00:28:55.943
We found an empty Percocet
bottle filled five days ago.

723
00:28:55.944 --> 00:28:57.111
What are you doing?
What are you doing?

724
00:28:57.112 --> 00:28:58.570
She's been uncooperative

725
00:28:58.571 --> 00:28:59.780
and combative since
we picked her up.

726
00:28:59.781 --> 00:29:01.198
Get off her. Let her go.

727
00:29:01.199 --> 00:29:02.741
Stop fighting.

728
00:29:02.742 --> 00:29:04.576
Calm the fuck down. or
I'm calling the cops.

729
00:29:04.577 --> 00:29:06.286
My meds at home aren't working!

730
00:29:06.287 --> 00:29:08.497
Please. I have sickle cell!

731
00:29:08.498 --> 00:29:10.290
OK. stop. Everybody stop.

732
00:29:10.291 --> 00:29:11.960
Stop!

733
00:29:12.669 --> 00:29:14.294
What's your name?

734
00:29:14.295 --> 00:29:16.547
It's Joyce. It's
Joyce St. Claire.

735
00:29:16.548 --> 00:29:18.757
Joyce. is this your
sickle cell pain?

736
00:29:18.758 --> 00:29:21.051
- Yes!
- 10 milligrams of IV morphine.

737
00:29:21.052 --> 00:29:22.386
- You really want 10?
- Yes.

738
00:29:22.387 --> 00:29:23.512
Repeat it in five
minutes if needed.

739
00:29:23.513 --> 00:29:24.888
And she needs a Dilaudid drip.

740
00:29:24.889 --> 00:29:25.973
This is a vaso-occlusive crisis!

741
00:29:25.974 --> 00:29:27.141
I'm so sorry this happened.

742
00:29:27.142 --> 00:29:28.767
You're going to be OK now.

743
00:29:28.768 --> 00:29:30.060
You're safe here.

744
00:29:30.061 --> 00:29:31.353
Come on.

745
00:29:31.354 --> 00:29:33.022
You're going to be
safe here. I promise.

746
00:29:33.023 --> 00:29:34.858
Just breathe. OK?

747
00:30:00.258 --> 00:30:01.800
Live wire hit his left forearm.

748
00:30:01.801 --> 00:30:03.510
shocked him once for v-fib.

749
00:30:03.511 --> 00:30:05.554
- Was there a power pole down?
- No. abandoned factory.

750
00:30:05.555 --> 00:30:06.638
We found bolt
cutters at his side.

751
00:30:06.639 --> 00:30:07.890
Got electrocuted.

752
00:30:07.891 --> 00:30:08.932
Was he trying to steal copper?

753
00:30:08.933 --> 00:30:09.933
Most likely.

754
00:30:09.934 --> 00:30:11.810
Powerline fried his arm.

755
00:30:11.811 --> 00:30:14.688
and the current through his
whole body stopped his heart.

756
00:30:14.689 --> 00:30:17.358
Ready?

757
00:30:17.359 --> 00:30:19.527
Steady. lift.

758
00:30:21.279 --> 00:30:24.073
Add a myoglobin and
a CK to the labs.

759
00:30:24.074 --> 00:30:26.116
Two liters normal
saline wide open.

760
00:30:26.117 --> 00:30:27.868
Dr. Santos. what are
we worried about?

761
00:30:27.869 --> 00:30:30.829
Um. rhabdomyolysis
from tissue damage

762
00:30:30.830 --> 00:30:33.791
can kill the kidneys. ongoing
risk of cardiac irritability.

763
00:30:33.792 --> 00:30:35.376
- Excellent.
- AP pads in place.

764
00:30:35.377 --> 00:30:37.086
Guy fell off a telephone pole?

765
00:30:37.087 --> 00:30:39.463
- No. he was on a platform.
- Boring.

766
00:30:39.464 --> 00:30:42.007
Cut into a live wire.

767
00:30:42.008 --> 00:30:43.676
Tense ventral compartment.

768
00:30:43.677 --> 00:30:45.094
Set up the STIC
pressure monitor.

769
00:30:45.095 --> 00:30:46.595
V-fib.

770
00:30:46.596 --> 00:30:48.055
- All right. charge to 300.
- Charge to 300.

771
00:30:48.056 --> 00:30:49.264
Am I running this or are you?

772
00:30:49.265 --> 00:30:51.393
- Sorry. reflex response.
- Clear.

773
00:30:52.352 --> 00:30:54.144
Ah. fuck!

774
00:30:54.145 --> 00:30:57.106
Sorry.

775
00:30:57.107 --> 00:30:59.692
So what... what happened?

776
00:30:59.693 --> 00:31:02.236
I bought it for my
girlfriend's dog.

777
00:31:02.237 --> 00:31:06.281
I work nights. and
he yaps all day long.

778
00:31:06.282 --> 00:31:08.992
And when I woke up.
I was wearing it.

779
00:31:08.993 --> 00:31:10.537
Stupid bitch!

780
00:31:11.996 --> 00:31:14.915
Sorry. sorry.

781
00:31:14.916 --> 00:31:17.418
I think she must
have used Krazy Glue.

782
00:31:17.419 --> 00:31:20.754
Yeah. it. um. it looks that way.

783
00:31:20.755 --> 00:31:22.506
Have you tried
removing the batteries?

784
00:31:22.507 --> 00:31:26.510
Of course. She
glued the case shut.

785
00:31:26.511 --> 00:31:29.388
All right. I think we have
a couple options. Gary.

786
00:31:29.389 --> 00:31:32.433
Um. we can try to find a
solvent that will dissolve

787
00:31:32.434 --> 00:31:34.893
or at least soften the glue
enough for you to peel it off

788
00:31:34.894 --> 00:31:36.979
without taking
your skin with it.

789
00:31:36.980 --> 00:31:39.231
Or. um...

790
00:31:39.232 --> 00:31:41.775
- Dr. Javadi?
- Um...

791
00:31:41.776 --> 00:31:44.862
I... I guess your skin cells
on your neck will naturally

792
00:31:44.863 --> 00:31:48.365
slough off and you should just
be able to remove it in time.

793
00:31:48.366 --> 00:31:51.410
- How much time?
- Um. couple of weeks. maybe.

794
00:31:51.411 --> 00:31:52.745
Couple weeks?

795
00:31:52.746 --> 00:31:54.371
I think this guy's got scurvy.

796
00:31:54.372 --> 00:31:55.497
What is he. a pirate?

797
00:31:55.498 --> 00:31:57.207
No. he's an unhoused man

798
00:31:57.208 --> 00:31:59.752
who lives almost exclusively
on dollar store ramen.

799
00:31:59.753 --> 00:32:02.338
There's perifollicular
hemorrhage. gingivitis.

800
00:32:02.339 --> 00:32:04.715
bleeding gums. and. um. yeah.

801
00:32:04.716 --> 00:32:06.133
no fruit or vegetables
in his diet.

802
00:32:06.134 --> 00:32:07.426
I suppose that could do it

803
00:32:07.427 --> 00:32:09.261
as long as you've
ruled out piracy.

804
00:32:09.262 --> 00:32:12.389
No parrot. no peg leg.
doesn't reek of sweat and rum?

805
00:32:12.390 --> 00:32:14.308
Well. now that you mention
it. there was a smell.

806
00:32:14.309 --> 00:32:17.311
Probably a pirate.

807
00:32:17.312 --> 00:32:18.729
Tell him to pick
up some vitamin C

808
00:32:18.730 --> 00:32:20.190
next time he docks
at a dollar store.

809
00:32:22.567 --> 00:32:24.234
I can't tell if you're joking.

810
00:32:24.235 --> 00:32:26.570
No. Captain Scurvy's got
a vitamin C deficiency.

811
00:32:26.571 --> 00:32:29.031
Cheapest way to fix it is
with a daily supplement.

812
00:32:29.032 --> 00:32:30.866
Captain Scurvy is another joke.

813
00:32:30.867 --> 00:32:32.868
- I'd like to think so.
- It's a good one.

814
00:32:32.869 --> 00:32:34.953
Dr. Langdon. Dr. King.
this is Arthur Carlson

815
00:32:34.954 --> 00:32:36.663
from Children.
Youth. and Families.

816
00:32:36.664 --> 00:32:38.540
He'd like to speak to the
parents of Tyler Jones.

817
00:32:38.541 --> 00:32:40.459
Right. right.

818
00:32:40.460 --> 00:32:42.961
Uh. Mel. would you mind showing
him to Kiara and the family?

819
00:32:42.962 --> 00:32:44.422
Mm. Yeah. right this way.

820
00:32:49.344 --> 00:32:51.095
- Beto?
- Hello. Doctor.

821
00:32:51.096 --> 00:32:54.473
- What are you doing here?
- I'm working day shifts now.

822
00:32:54.474 --> 00:32:56.392
Didn't you retire a
couple of years ago?

823
00:32:56.393 --> 00:32:57.893
No.

824
00:32:57.894 --> 00:33:01.105
- I have to work today.
- Right.

825
00:33:01.106 --> 00:33:02.648
Right. Just stay
right here. OK?

826
00:33:02.649 --> 00:33:04.566
I... I have a lot
of cleaning to do.

827
00:33:04.567 --> 00:33:06.527
Yeah. no. I'll be
just one second.

828
00:33:06.528 --> 00:33:08.862
Hey. Doc. Doc! How
about a sandwich?

829
00:33:08.863 --> 00:33:10.656
Sure. Earl. Turkey.
no egg salad.

830
00:33:10.657 --> 00:33:12.909
I got you. Just
give me one minute.

831
00:33:15.078 --> 00:33:16.829
So Beto said he's working here?

832
00:33:16.830 --> 00:33:18.372
Yeah. he just started wandering.

833
00:33:18.373 --> 00:33:20.541
Fortunately. he always
winds up back here.

834
00:33:20.542 --> 00:33:22.251
He thinks he still
works in the ED.

835
00:33:22.252 --> 00:33:23.752
I called his family.

836
00:33:23.753 --> 00:33:25.045
They usually pick him
up after a few hours.

837
00:33:25.046 --> 00:33:26.171
Really?

838
00:33:26.172 --> 00:33:27.631
Yeah. It gives them a break.

839
00:33:27.632 --> 00:33:29.091
And look at him. He's
talking to people.

840
00:33:29.092 --> 00:33:31.510
feeling useful.
getting some exercise.

841
00:33:31.511 --> 00:33:33.137
Hell. I wish I was that happy.

842
00:33:33.138 --> 00:33:34.763
You think he's any
good at catching rats?

843
00:33:34.764 --> 00:33:37.433
- Stop.
- Oh. Earl wants a sandwich.

844
00:33:37.434 --> 00:33:39.393
He always wants a sandwich.

845
00:33:39.394 --> 00:33:40.853
Hey. check it out.

846
00:33:40.854 --> 00:33:42.396
I got my kids a puppy.

847
00:33:42.397 --> 00:33:44.565
Cute. Hope that
wasn't your idea.

848
00:33:44.566 --> 00:33:46.358
- Why?
- Seriously?

849
00:33:46.359 --> 00:33:47.693
You really think your wife

850
00:33:47.694 --> 00:33:49.111
needs anything else
to take care of?

851
00:33:49.112 --> 00:33:51.238
- Abby loves dogs.
- I love penguins.

852
00:33:51.239 --> 00:33:52.823
It doesn't mean I want
to take care of one.

853
00:33:52.824 --> 00:33:54.366
I'm pretty sure it's
illegal to own a penguin.

854
00:33:54.367 --> 00:33:55.868
Pretty sure you're
missing the point.

855
00:33:55.869 --> 00:33:57.327
The point is Tanner promised

856
00:33:57.328 --> 00:33:58.579
he would take care of it.

857
00:33:58.580 --> 00:34:01.666
A four-year-old? Yeah. OK.

858
00:34:06.921 --> 00:34:08.547
How's she doing?

859
00:34:08.548 --> 00:34:11.593
Still breathing
after 20 of morphine.

860
00:34:13.803 --> 00:34:15.138
How's the pain. Joyce?

861
00:34:16.306 --> 00:34:17.848
A little better.

862
00:34:17.849 --> 00:34:19.892
We've ordered an
exchange transfusion.

863
00:34:19.893 --> 00:34:22.394
Mm. Figured I needed that.

864
00:34:22.395 --> 00:34:24.938
What's your normal
regimen at home?

865
00:34:24.939 --> 00:34:28.859
90 of extended-release
morphine every 12 hours

866
00:34:28.860 --> 00:34:31.195
and oxycodone for
breakthrough pain.

867
00:34:31.196 --> 00:34:33.697
but it wasn't working.

868
00:34:33.698 --> 00:34:36.825
Starting IV Dilaudid
of four an hour.

869
00:34:36.826 --> 00:34:39.203
You can press this button
if you need a little extra.

870
00:34:39.204 --> 00:34:42.831
That only works once an hour.
though. so don't go crazy.

871
00:34:42.832 --> 00:34:45.752
- Could I confer with you?
- Yeah.

872
00:34:54.511 --> 00:34:57.054
You seem surprised
by the opioid dosage.

873
00:34:57.055 --> 00:34:59.598
- It seemed a little high.
- So was her pain.

874
00:34:59.599 --> 00:35:01.183
How do you know she's
not drug-seeking?

875
00:35:01.184 --> 00:35:03.060
You can't fake a
hemoglobin of 6.

876
00:35:03.061 --> 00:35:05.104
Do you know what sickle cell
crisis does to the body?

877
00:35:05.105 --> 00:35:06.647
Blood cells get caught and
plug up your capillaries

878
00:35:06.648 --> 00:35:08.357
and deprive all your
cells of oxygen.

879
00:35:08.358 --> 00:35:11.193
It's been described as an
electrical stabbing pain

880
00:35:11.194 --> 00:35:12.695
that feels like it's
breaking your bones

881
00:35:12.696 --> 00:35:15.447
and flushing glass
through your body.

882
00:35:15.448 --> 00:35:17.282
I never thought of it like that.

883
00:35:17.283 --> 00:35:18.659
Little empathy goes a long way

884
00:35:18.660 --> 00:35:20.412
with those suffering
in real pain.

885
00:35:22.539 --> 00:35:23.956
- Yeah.
- Don't worry.

886
00:35:23.957 --> 00:35:25.457
You'll get good at
spotting the fakers.

887
00:35:25.458 --> 00:35:27.334
and half the time.
all those people need

888
00:35:27.335 --> 00:35:29.921
is someone to really listen
to them and hear their story.

889
00:35:31.464 --> 00:35:33.007
Mm-hmm.

890
00:35:33.008 --> 00:35:36.885
Interior compartment
pressure is 49.

891
00:35:36.886 --> 00:35:38.637
Burn caused massive swelling.

892
00:35:38.638 --> 00:35:40.514
What does he need. Dr. Santos?

893
00:35:40.515 --> 00:35:43.475
Fasciotomy. but he still
has a radial pulse.

894
00:35:43.476 --> 00:35:45.519
Pressure would have to be
over 100 to lose the pulse.

895
00:35:45.520 --> 00:35:47.187
and at that point.
he'd lose the arm.

896
00:35:47.188 --> 00:35:49.231
49 is enough to destroy
all the nerves and muscles

897
00:35:49.232 --> 00:35:51.108
in a matter of hours.

898
00:35:51.109 --> 00:35:52.818
- Compartment pressure's 49?
- Yeah.

899
00:35:52.819 --> 00:35:54.778
I'm going to make the
initial incision down here.

900
00:35:54.779 --> 00:35:56.488
Ortho can finish
it up in the OR.

901
00:35:56.489 --> 00:35:58.323
Good plan. I'll let them know.

902
00:35:58.324 --> 00:36:00.075
- Hey. Robby.
- Always good to see you. Fred.

903
00:36:00.076 --> 00:36:01.368
- How do you like my rock star?
- She's pretty good.

904
00:36:01.369 --> 00:36:03.954
She has a great teacher.

905
00:36:03.955 --> 00:36:05.914
Sterile gloves for Dr. Santos.

906
00:36:05.915 --> 00:36:09.209
Oh. we don't teach forearm
fasciotomies to our residents.

907
00:36:09.210 --> 00:36:11.170
What if she's all
alone somewhere someday

908
00:36:11.171 --> 00:36:13.381
with no backup?

909
00:36:15.467 --> 00:36:18.594
This is the path to
avoid the median nerve

910
00:36:18.595 --> 00:36:20.804
and all major vessels.

911
00:36:20.805 --> 00:36:23.098
Maybe just watch the first time.

912
00:36:23.099 --> 00:36:25.517
She'll hold the blade. I'll cut.

913
00:36:25.518 --> 00:36:27.062
10 blade to Dr. Santos.

914
00:36:30.690 --> 00:36:33.067
We'll start proximal.

915
00:36:33.068 --> 00:36:34.526
How much pressure?

916
00:36:34.527 --> 00:36:37.655
Just about this much.

917
00:36:41.910 --> 00:36:43.286
Mm-hmm.

918
00:36:45.997 --> 00:36:48.541
Through the skin and sub-Q.

919
00:36:53.046 --> 00:36:54.422
Good.

920
00:36:58.677 --> 00:37:00.552
How they making out?

921
00:37:00.553 --> 00:37:02.263
They're still talking.

922
00:37:03.765 --> 00:37:05.766
- You OK?
- Yeah. for sure.

923
00:37:05.767 --> 00:37:07.935
I just... I hate seeing
families torn apart.

924
00:37:07.936 --> 00:37:09.520
Oh. they'll be fine.

925
00:37:09.521 --> 00:37:11.980
- How can you be sure?
- They're white.

926
00:37:11.981 --> 00:37:14.274
Probably get off with
a slap on the wrist.

927
00:37:14.275 --> 00:37:16.777
If they weren't. she'd
probably lose her child

928
00:37:16.778 --> 00:37:20.406
and he'd end up
going to jail. but...

929
00:37:20.407 --> 00:37:23.367
Sorry. I did a
fellowship in cynicism.

930
00:37:23.368 --> 00:37:24.868
You sure you're OK?

931
00:37:24.869 --> 00:37:26.955
100%. I'm just going
to get some air.

932
00:37:32.836 --> 00:37:35.671
I am a savage. classy. bougie.

933
00:37:35.672 --> 00:37:38.549
ratchet. sassy. moody. nasty.

934
00:37:38.550 --> 00:37:40.510
I am a savage...

935
00:37:41.469 --> 00:37:42.886
I need help!

936
00:37:42.887 --> 00:37:44.013
I got shot.

937
00:37:44.014 --> 00:37:45.265
Can you guys help?

938
00:37:46.141 --> 00:37:47.474
What's your name?

939
00:37:47.475 --> 00:37:48.642
Alex.

940
00:37:48.643 --> 00:37:50.853
OK. Alex. let me take a look.

941
00:37:50.854 --> 00:37:52.229
It fucking hurts.

942
00:37:52.230 --> 00:37:54.189
Oh. I know. All right.

943
00:37:54.190 --> 00:37:55.399
We're going to take
good care of you.

944
00:37:55.400 --> 00:37:57.067
- Yeah.
- You guys got it?

945
00:37:57.068 --> 00:37:59.278
Let me get you up here. Alex.

946
00:37:59.279 --> 00:38:00.988
I got you.

947
00:38:00.989 --> 00:38:02.364
I have an abdominal GSW

948
00:38:02.365 --> 00:38:05.159
in the ambulance
bay. code trauma now.

949
00:38:05.160 --> 00:38:07.786
GSW just got dumped by
a homeboy ambulance.

950
00:38:07.787 --> 00:38:10.831
- You got this?
- Yeah. go.

951
00:38:10.832 --> 00:38:14.169
2 grams of Ancef.
Ortho's on their way.

952
00:38:17.964 --> 00:38:20.591
Systolic's only 80.
14 gauge left AC.

953
00:38:20.592 --> 00:38:21.717
We got two units of whole blood

954
00:38:21.718 --> 00:38:23.052
going on the rapid infuser.

955
00:38:23.053 --> 00:38:24.386
Call the OR.
We'll be right up.

956
00:38:24.387 --> 00:38:25.721
Lungs up.

957
00:38:25.722 --> 00:38:26.930
Do you take
medications every day?

958
00:38:26.931 --> 00:38:28.849
- Any allergies?
- No.

959
00:38:28.850 --> 00:38:30.309
Morrison's is full of
blood. You see that?

960
00:38:30.310 --> 00:38:32.186
- Yeah.
- Tore up his liver.

961
00:38:32.187 --> 00:38:33.604
- What's his name?
- Alex.

962
00:38:33.605 --> 00:38:34.980
Alex. you've lost
a lot of blood.

963
00:38:34.981 --> 00:38:36.315
You need to go to
surgery right away.

964
00:38:36.316 --> 00:38:37.316
Am I going to die?

965
00:38:37.317 --> 00:38:38.817
Not now that I'm here.

966
00:38:38.818 --> 00:38:40.110
Spoken with the
humility of a surgeon.

967
00:38:40.111 --> 00:38:41.445
OR's ready. How's he doing?

968
00:38:41.446 --> 00:38:43.155
- BP is coming up a bit.
- Let's go.

969
00:38:43.156 --> 00:38:44.948
- Can you call my mom?
- Yep.

970
00:38:44.949 --> 00:38:47.576
- She's the "ICE" on my cell.
- Of course. of course.

971
00:38:47.577 --> 00:38:50.162
So he didn't have
to wait for an OR?

972
00:38:50.163 --> 00:38:51.997
No. we're a trauma center.

973
00:38:51.998 --> 00:38:54.416
We always keep one OR
stocked and ready to go.

974
00:38:54.417 --> 00:38:58.087
Well. that's awesome!

975
00:38:58.088 --> 00:39:01.090
What... what happens if there
are multiple traumas needing OR?

976
00:39:01.091 --> 00:39:02.717
We get a lot busier.

977
00:39:04.636 --> 00:39:06.136
<i>Mr. Milton. I'm sorry.</i>

978
00:39:06.137 --> 00:39:07.846
We had to move
you into the hall.

979
00:39:07.847 --> 00:39:09.807
I know it gets pretty
chaotic and noisy out here.

980
00:39:09.808 --> 00:39:12.309
Mr. Milton?

981
00:39:12.310 --> 00:39:14.771
Hey. hey. Bennet.
wake up for me.

982
00:39:17.190 --> 00:39:19.984
Oh. shit. shit. shit. Um.
I need a little help here!

983
00:39:21.194 --> 00:39:22.444
Help!

984
00:39:22.445 --> 00:39:24.029
When did you check on him last?

985
00:39:24.030 --> 00:39:25.656
I don't know. around
half an hour ago at most.

986
00:39:25.657 --> 00:39:27.157
- I was waiting on labs.
- What's going on?

987
00:39:27.158 --> 00:39:28.826
It's my gallstone
guy. You saw his EKGs.

988
00:39:28.827 --> 00:39:31.495
Unknown downtime. He was
sleeping in the hall.

989
00:39:31.496 --> 00:39:33.498
Crash cart. let's go!

990
00:39:36.584 --> 00:39:38.420
I got it.

991
00:39:40.964 --> 00:39:42.507
Hold compressions.

992
00:39:44.676 --> 00:39:46.218
Asystole.

993
00:39:46.219 --> 00:39:49.972
Resume compressions. amp of epi.

994
00:39:49.973 --> 00:39:51.432
Slower. slower
tempo. slower tempo.

995
00:39:51.433 --> 00:39:53.392
- Should I intubate?
- No. Drop an LMA.

996
00:39:53.393 --> 00:39:56.061
We don't want to
hold compressions.

997
00:39:56.062 --> 00:39:58.147
Pupils are fixed and dilated.

998
00:39:58.148 --> 00:39:59.607
He's been down a long time.

999
00:40:11.661 --> 00:40:12.995
How we doing in here?

1000
00:40:12.996 --> 00:40:14.538
So much better.

1001
00:40:14.539 --> 00:40:17.124
Dr. Mohan. this is
my wife. Ondine.

1002
00:40:17.125 --> 00:40:19.752
Dr. Samira Mohan. Nice
to meet you. Ondine.

1003
00:40:19.753 --> 00:40:21.920
- Thank you for helping her.
- Of course.

1004
00:40:21.921 --> 00:40:24.715
And. again. I'm so sorry
about how you were treated

1005
00:40:24.716 --> 00:40:26.383
when you first arrived.

1006
00:40:26.384 --> 00:40:27.760
Not everyone who works here

1007
00:40:27.761 --> 00:40:29.678
is accustomed to dealing
with sickle cell.

1008
00:40:29.679 --> 00:40:31.138
We will be doing
everything possible

1009
00:40:31.139 --> 00:40:33.807
from here on in to
manage Joyce's crisis.

1010
00:40:33.808 --> 00:40:35.684
In the meantime. can
I get you anything?

1011
00:40:35.685 --> 00:40:36.727
I'm fine.

1012
00:40:36.728 --> 00:40:38.228
- Ondine?
- No. thank you.

1013
00:40:38.229 --> 00:40:39.646
OK. Well. have the
nurses come find me

1014
00:40:39.647 --> 00:40:40.815
if you need anything.

1015
00:40:43.568 --> 00:40:45.944
Take slow. deep
breaths for me. Ian.

1016
00:40:45.945 --> 00:40:48.947
They ordered a neb. 5
albuterol. 125 solumedrol.

1017
00:40:48.948 --> 00:40:50.574
All right.

1018
00:40:50.575 --> 00:40:52.242
Keep an eye on him and
present to Dr. Langdon.

1019
00:40:52.243 --> 00:40:54.328
- OK.
- OK. great.

1020
00:40:54.329 --> 00:40:56.538
I'll see you back in triage
once he settles down.

1021
00:40:56.539 --> 00:40:58.457
Yeah.

1022
00:40:58.458 --> 00:40:59.583
OK. let's take this off.

1023
00:40:59.584 --> 00:41:01.001
All right. hang in there. Ian.

1024
00:41:01.002 --> 00:41:02.837
This should really
help your asthma.

1025
00:41:12.806 --> 00:41:13.931
How can I help you. hon?

1026
00:41:13.932 --> 00:41:15.307
Um. I'm looking
for Dr. Langdon.

1027
00:41:15.308 --> 00:41:17.143
Yeah. let me see where he is.

1028
00:41:20.689 --> 00:41:22.481
Dr. Langdon. we
have a med student

1029
00:41:22.482 --> 00:41:24.109
at Central looking for you.

1030
00:41:25.694 --> 00:41:27.403
Copy that. He's
headed this way.

1031
00:41:27.404 --> 00:41:28.571
Thanks.

1032
00:41:29.864 --> 00:41:31.115
Hey. Crash.

1033
00:41:31.116 --> 00:41:33.617
You missed a pretty
cool fasciotomy.

1034
00:41:33.618 --> 00:41:34.910
I'm not sure I'd be describing

1035
00:41:34.911 --> 00:41:36.495
a fasciotomy as cool.

1036
00:41:36.496 --> 00:41:39.206
You would if you were
the one who did it.

1037
00:41:39.207 --> 00:41:42.335
How's it going out in
the arrivals lounge?

1038
00:41:44.337 --> 00:41:47.256
Do you know anything
about Dr. McKay?

1039
00:41:47.257 --> 00:41:49.591
I've been here for
less than two hours.

1040
00:41:49.592 --> 00:41:52.803
I don't know anybody.
including you.

1041
00:41:52.804 --> 00:41:55.681
I thought you were some
kind of kid genius.

1042
00:41:55.682 --> 00:41:58.100
I'm like any other
third-year med student.

1043
00:41:58.101 --> 00:42:01.020
Clearly.

1044
00:42:01.021 --> 00:42:02.479
Hey. I'm just trying
to break the ice.

1045
00:42:02.480 --> 00:42:04.523
I'm not trying to annoy you.

1046
00:42:04.524 --> 00:42:06.442
And yet. you're still
calling me Crash

1047
00:42:06.443 --> 00:42:07.860
when I asked you not to.

1048
00:42:07.861 --> 00:42:09.653
Really? You're still on that?

1049
00:42:09.654 --> 00:42:11.031
Still on that.

1050
00:42:12.365 --> 00:42:15.242
Yep. OK. sorry.

1051
00:42:15.243 --> 00:42:20.205
I had no idea genius
was so sensitive.

1052
00:42:20.206 --> 00:42:23.292
But I get it. Big
brain. big feelings.

1053
00:42:23.293 --> 00:42:24.752
Makes total sense.

1054
00:42:24.753 --> 00:42:26.671
I'll try to be softer.

1055
00:42:50.653 --> 00:42:51.945
We switch out every few minutes.

1056
00:42:51.946 --> 00:42:53.614
- You can take a break.
- I'm fine.

1057
00:42:53.615 --> 00:42:54.908
Hold compressions.

1058
00:42:56.910 --> 00:42:58.494
Still in asystole.

1059
00:42:58.495 --> 00:43:00.996
Resume compressions.

1060
00:43:00.997 --> 00:43:02.373
Should we shock him?

1061
00:43:02.374 --> 00:43:03.791
You don't shock asystole.

1062
00:43:03.792 --> 00:43:05.084
It could be fine v-fib.

1063
00:43:05.085 --> 00:43:07.753
- Not a chance.
- OK.

1064
00:43:07.754 --> 00:43:08.962
Uh. when was his last epi?

1065
00:43:08.963 --> 00:43:10.673
- Three minutes ago.
- OK.

1066
00:43:10.674 --> 00:43:12.091
Well. ACLS says every three
to five minute. right?

1067
00:43:12.092 --> 00:43:14.677
- So let's push another round.
- Fine.

1068
00:43:14.678 --> 00:43:17.513
Robby. Mr. Spencer's adult
children are asking for you.

1069
00:43:17.514 --> 00:43:19.431
And the parents of Nick Bradley.

1070
00:43:19.432 --> 00:43:21.392
the fentanyl overdose. also
want to speak with you.

1071
00:43:21.393 --> 00:43:22.768
OK.

1072
00:43:22.769 --> 00:43:25.979
Three rounds of epi
and then call it.

1073
00:43:25.980 --> 00:43:28.524
Mr. Spencer's maxed
out on BiPAP. 25 on 10.

1074
00:43:28.525 --> 00:43:31.528
- Sats?
- Not great. High 80s.

1075
00:43:34.489 --> 00:43:36.115
Hi. I heard you
wanted to talk to me.

1076
00:43:36.116 --> 00:43:37.950
Yeah. That alarm
kept going off.

1077
00:43:37.951 --> 00:43:40.954
Yeah. Why don't
we step outside?

1078
00:43:41.663 --> 00:43:43.288
The alarm is for low oxygen.

1079
00:43:43.289 --> 00:43:45.582
Does he need more
of that. um. BiPAP?

1080
00:43:45.583 --> 00:43:47.626
I'm afraid that's
as high as we go.

1081
00:43:47.627 --> 00:43:49.420
So the decision at
this point is...

1082
00:43:49.421 --> 00:43:52.382
We want you to put our father
on the breathing machine.

1083
00:43:54.217 --> 00:43:55.884
Even though that goes
against his desires

1084
00:43:55.885 --> 00:43:58.220
to not be intubated?

1085
00:43:58.221 --> 00:44:00.723
We're not ready to let go yet.

1086
00:44:00.724 --> 00:44:03.810
And if your father is?

1087
00:44:05.353 --> 00:44:06.812
He was a stubborn son of a bitch

1088
00:44:06.813 --> 00:44:09.356
who would never have
given up on either of us.

1089
00:44:09.357 --> 00:44:12.151
We're not giving up on him.

1090
00:44:12.152 --> 00:44:14.153
You're absolutely
certain you want

1091
00:44:14.154 --> 00:44:16.634
to put your father through this
after everything I've told you?

1092
00:44:20.869 --> 00:44:24.913
I may have to honor
his advanced directive.

1093
00:44:24.914 --> 00:44:29.043
No. you have to honor our
durable power for health care.

1094
00:44:29.044 --> 00:44:32.505
If not. we can talk to
your hospital attorney.

1095
00:44:35.050 --> 00:44:37.301
Jereme. you're on
board with this?

1096
00:44:37.302 --> 00:44:39.512
Yeah. I guess so.

1097
00:44:41.222 --> 00:44:43.891
OK. You can sit with
him until we're ready.

1098
00:44:43.892 --> 00:44:46.061
- And when will that be?
- Momentarily.

1099
00:44:57.697 --> 00:44:59.031
Please don't tell me

1100
00:44:59.032 --> 00:45:00.366
you're going to
intubate that poor man.

1101
00:45:00.367 --> 00:45:02.076
It's what the family wants.

1102
00:45:02.077 --> 00:45:03.827
So what? They want
to torture him?

1103
00:45:03.828 --> 00:45:06.330
I explained all that.

1104
00:45:06.331 --> 00:45:10.292
If I co-sign. you can
override their durable power.

1105
00:45:10.293 --> 00:45:12.127
They're threatening to go
to the hospital attorney.

1106
00:45:12.128 --> 00:45:13.587
Let them. Call the
Ethics Committee.

1107
00:45:13.588 --> 00:45:14.838
They'll agree with us.

1108
00:45:14.839 --> 00:45:16.173
No. no. you're probably right.

1109
00:45:16.174 --> 00:45:17.675
But we don't have
that kind of time.

1110
00:45:17.676 --> 00:45:19.426
We are stuck.

1111
00:45:19.427 --> 00:45:22.514
- What are you talking about?
- Shit.

1112
00:45:24.766 --> 00:45:26.141
What?

1113
00:45:26.142 --> 00:45:27.559
I got to go tell those parents

1114
00:45:27.560 --> 00:45:30.062
their 18-year-old
son is brain-dead.

1115
00:45:30.063 --> 00:45:32.690
- Want me to come with you?
- No. It's OK.

1116
00:45:32.691 --> 00:45:34.024
What are you going to say?

1117
00:45:34.025 --> 00:45:35.442
I'm going to say
that it's likely.

1118
00:45:35.443 --> 00:45:36.985
but we still need
to do an apnea test

1119
00:45:36.986 --> 00:45:40.072
and a cerebral perfusion study.

1120
00:45:40.073 --> 00:45:41.782
There's no cranial
nerve activity.

1121
00:45:41.783 --> 00:45:45.619
- Those people need some hope.
- False hope.

1122
00:45:45.620 --> 00:45:47.746
- Hope is hope.
- Is it?

1123
00:45:47.747 --> 00:45:51.333
What. are we praying
for miracles today?

1124
00:45:51.334 --> 00:45:52.876
They need time to process

1125
00:45:52.877 --> 00:45:55.879
before they can accept
what's happening.

1126
00:45:55.880 --> 00:45:59.299
You ever consider
taking that advice?

1127
00:45:59.300 --> 00:46:02.428
Physician. heal thyself.

1128
00:46:02.429 --> 00:46:04.014
Don't you have patients?

1129
00:46:26.619 --> 00:46:29.288
No. no. no. no. no. no.
People wake up from comas.

1130
00:46:29.289 --> 00:46:31.415
You can wake him up.

1131
00:46:31.416 --> 00:46:33.667
You can do that. You
can... you can shock...

1132
00:46:33.668 --> 00:46:36.254
you can... you can
shock him back.

1133
00:46:41.760 --> 00:46:44.679
Nick.

1134
00:46:52.312 --> 00:46:53.812
Hey. hey. hey.

1135
00:46:53.813 --> 00:46:55.564
Hey. hey. hey. hey. hey.

1136
00:46:55.565 --> 00:46:57.567
Nick.

1137
00:46:59.819 --> 00:47:03.531
Please. no!

1138
00:48:09.014 --> 00:48:10.973
No change.

1139
00:48:10.974 --> 00:48:12.474
No pericardial effusion.

1140
00:48:12.475 --> 00:48:16.437
no tension pneumothorax.
no cardiac activity.

1141
00:48:16.438 --> 00:48:18.689
Try calcium. Could
be hyperkalemia.

1142
00:48:18.690 --> 00:48:20.733
No. his potassium was normal.

1143
00:48:20.734 --> 00:48:23.277
- Ready to call this?
- Not yet.

1144
00:48:23.278 --> 00:48:25.279
Dr. Robby said
three rounds of epi.

1145
00:48:25.280 --> 00:48:26.864
It's time. Let's
push another amp.

1146
00:48:26.865 --> 00:48:28.450
This one could do it.

1147
00:48:31.077 --> 00:48:32.203
OK.

1147
